There is one problematic case that can be seen pretty frequently in IMDG with SQL - when the same field is present in both key and value. The common motivation for this is data co-location for joins. E.g.:
PersonKey {
    Long id;
    Long deptId;
}
PersonValue {
    ...
    Long deptId;
}

Is there a way to write to both fields in our case?
